documentation.author: Steve Wade
documentation.purpose: This rule is designed to send an email message to the BayCare Behavioral Health Director of Medical Services and Quality when an order for a multiple antipsychotic is signed by a Physician, Physician Assistant or Nurse Practitioner. The patient needs to have a Medical Service of DPUPSYCH or Pyschiatric and been admited >72 hours before the order is signed for the email to be sent. The rule will not trigger when the order entry field for PRN Reason is populated.
documentation.explanation:
Evoke: ORDER EVENT Order List: consists of 21 antipsychotic meds (see below) Order Entry: The rule will not trigger when the order entry field for PRN Reason is populated Positions: User needs to be a Physician, Physician Assistant or Nurse Practitioner Encounter: Must be Medical Service DPUPSYCH or Psychiatric Encounter: Must be admitted > 4320 minute ago (72 hours) Action: When conditions are true, email message will be sent
21 Triggering Antipsychotic meds: Aripiprazole Asenapine chlorpromazine clozapine fluphenazine haloperidol iloperidone loxapine lurasidone mesoridazine molindone OLANZapine Paliperidone Perphenazine Pimozide QUEtiapine Risperidone Thioridazine Thiothixene Trifluoperazine ziprasidone

templateDefinitions.name: EKS_ORDERS_FIND_L
templateDefinitions.definition: orders exist ORD_METHOD OPT_ORDERS with order status of OPT_ORDER_STATUS on OPT_SCOPE OPT_LINK whose date criteria is OPT_QUAL OPT_TIME_NUM OPT_TIME_UNIT from the anchor OPT_ANCHOR_DT_TM.
